 is similar to one of the treatment arms in our study, see below).
 In particular, using rice farmers in Bangladesh as a case, they compare
 two types of site-specific fertilizer recommendationsâ€”community-level recommend
ations and plot-specific recommendations based on individual soil testsâ€”and
 compare this to government provided recommendations.
 They find limited effects, except perhaps for a reduction in application
 error (difference between recommended quantity of a particular nutrient
 and quantity used).
 That is, some farmers were using more than the recommended TSP and as a
 result of the intervention cut back.
 Some even appear to over-react and stop using TSP altogether, leading to
 lower yield.
 They also find indications that farmers adapt seed use to match baseline
 fertilizer use.
 Another study with a soil test treatment are is 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "gars2015confidence"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, which shows that plot-level soil testing and tailored input recommendations
